{"type":"message","id":"00b137b1","parentId":"4e709a8b","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:28:45.480Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user says \"执行这个任务\" and previously sent \"2\". I think there might be a numbered list somewhere that I'm not seeing. Maybe they want to execute the 2nd task from a list? Or maybe the \"2\" from before was a selection. Let me check the current cursor task queue to see if there's a numbered task list, and also check what \"2\" might refer to.\n\nActually, I don't have context of what \"2\" refers to. The user might be referring to a message or task number from a previous interaction. Let me ask what \"2\" refers to, or check the pending tasks.\n\nWait, maybe \"2\" refers to the 2nd task in a list I showed earlier? Or maybe the user is saying \"执行这个任务\" referring to something specific. \n\nI'm not sure what \"2\" means without more context. The user seems to want me to execute something, but I'm missing the reference point. Maybe \"2\" is a task ID or序号 from an earlier message that I didn't see, or perhaps they want me to run the cursor daemon with a specific task number."},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 不知道\"2\"指的是哪个任务，能说一下任务名称或者从哪来的列表吗？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775057316499}}
